# Cyberland Mod System Lifecycle

Use ECS systems with clear lifecycle boundaries and ownership.

## Clean, modern ECS patterns

- Prefer data-oriented, composition-first design with small components and focused systems.
- Keep systems single-purpose and phase-appropriate (input, simulation, presentation, lighting should be separate).
- Model gameplay state in ECS components (including singleton/state entities) instead of ad-hoc session objects when practical.
- Favor query/chunk iteration patterns over hard-coded entity wiring when roles can be expressed by components.
- **Prefer `IParallelSystem` + `RegisterParallel`** for simulation and rendering systems; use `IParallelEarlyUpdate` / `IParallelFixedUpdate` / `IParallelLateUpdate` so the host supplies `ParallelOptions`. Keep `ISystem` + `RegisterSerial` when the whole phase callback must be single-threaded. Keyboard/gamepad polling can live **between** inner `Parallel.ForEach` barriers inside `IParallelEarlyUpdate` (scheduler thread); see **`mods/Cyberland.Demo` `InputSystem`**. This aligns with **cyberland-design-goals** parallelism and performance pillars.
- Design for parallel-friendly execution where safe: avoid hidden shared mutable state and keep write-sets explicit.
- Use stable naming and folder organization (`Components` / `Systems`) so responsibilities are obvious at a glance.

## Lifecycle split

- Put one-time setup in `OnStart`: validate dependencies, cache **`World`** when random access is needed, resolve singleton **`EntityId`**s via queries—not **`Components<T>()`** store fields for ongoing iteration (see **cyberland-mod-patterns-hdr** and **cyberland-ecs-world-access**).
- Keep parallel phase methods (`OnParallelEarlyUpdate` / `OnParallelFixedUpdate` / `OnParallelLateUpdate`) or serial phase methods (`OnEarlyUpdate` / `OnFixedUpdate` / `OnLateUpdate`) focused on per-tick state changes only.
- Do not perform first-frame lazy initialization in `*Update`; no "if not initialized then init" paths. Avoid `_resolved` / `_initialized` gates in phase methods—**`OnStart`** already ran for that registration.

## Required init behavior

- If a required dependency for initialization is missing in `OnStart` (for example `Host.Renderer`, required entities/components, or required services), report an engine error and fail fast.
- Prefer explicit diagnostics that name the system and missing dependency.

## Component-system association

- Keep component ownership tight: each system should read/write a small, intentional component set.
- Avoid "god systems" that mix unrelated domains (input, simulation, UI, lighting) in one class.
- Static visual configuration belongs to startup/setup; runtime systems should mutate only dynamic fields.

## Example pattern

```csharp
public void OnStart(World world, ChunkQueryAll query)
{
    _ = query;
    _ = _host.Renderer ?? throw new InvalidOperationException("Renderer required for startup init.");
    InitializeStaticVisualState(world);
}

public void OnParallelLateUpdate(ChunkQueryAll query, float deltaSeconds, ParallelOptions parallelOptions)
{
    _ = parallelOptions;
    foreach (var chunk in query) { /* partition row work when truly parallel */ }
}
```

